latest_comments.comments: Pete is so smart and well spoken. I loved this interview.

This is interesting. As an American living in Europe (for the last 11 years) this topic of measuring distance in minutes comes up quite often. Not to Speak for all the countries (I live in Sweden, and used to Live in Germany) but I often get asked “what’s the deal with People in the US telling you minutes when you ask how far away something is?” There is actually a Finnish comedian that has an entire bit about it.  The only conclusion I could make was that since in the US most everyone has a car we are able to streamline the “well by car it will take this many minutes” where as in most European countries people walk, bike and take public transit a lot more so knowing the distance in actual kilometers allows them to make the educated choice as to what form of transportation will best get them to their destination.
I'm a Canadian....and I would totally vote for Mayor Pete!
I have taken the train way more than I have flown. High speed rail would keep that trend going!
That's why in Texas we tell you everything in how long it'll take you to get there.🔥

description:
We get asked DAILY… “Where do I begin?”

Your #1 financial priority is a 3-6 month emergency fund in a high yield savings account (or HYSA). 💸 It’s a non-negotiable no matter what stage of your financial journey you’re in.

Yes, BEFORE you invest and BEFORE you pay off debt.

👉The TL;DR— you’re losing money with your regular savings account, and you need to open an HYSA yesterday.

Let us explain...

But why an HYSA over your typical savings account? 🧐

1️⃣ Your typical savings account earns you just 0.06% at your local bank — literal pennies.

2️⃣ A high-yield savings account, on the other hand, can earn you SO MUCH MORE.

The longer you wait to open up a high-yield savings account, the more money you lose.

Comment HYSA100 below for our recommendation!!
